
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to convert a base64 encoded audio data retrieved from an HTTP POST request to its original binary format. The [convert] slot is used with the [type] argument set to "from-base64", targeting the specific node containing the base64 data through the expression [x:@http.post/*/content/*/choices/0/*/message/*/audio/*/data].
convert:x:@http.post/*/content/*/choices/0/*/message/*/audio/*/data
   type:from-base64
